5|$|In {{the early}} 1600s England was at peace and Pendennis was neglected; {{reportedly}} the garrison's <b>pay</b> <b>was</b> {{two years in}} arrears, forcing them to gather limpets from the shoreline for food. Nonetheless, a new Italian-styled gatehouse {{was added to the}} castle, probably in 1611. War with Spain broke out again 1624 and a new defensive line, with bastions and artillery, was built across the peninsula in 1627.|$|E
5|$|Law {{originally}} {{found a job}} as {{a traveling}} carpet salesman. He continued until he discovered that his employer was misrepresenting domestic rugs as being imported and was also charging premium prices. His next employer, an outfitter of steamships and hotels, went out of business in the 1860s, when the American Civil War affected the business. Law struggled through unemployment, and even while working, <b>pay</b> <b>was</b> low. At one point, Law was employed at a store and was making eight dollars a week.|$|E
